IPIC First-Half Profit Triples on Financial Instruments Income

-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 
2011-10-18T11:35:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/ipic-first-half-profit-triples-on-financial-instruments-income.html
International Petroleum Investment
Co., an Abu Dhabi government-backed investor, said first-half
profit tripled on income from financial instruments.  Profit attributable to equity holders of the parent surged
to $988.4 million from $328.4 million a year earlier, the
company said in a  statement  posted on the London Stock Exchange
today. Revenue rose to $8.63 billion from $7.38 billion.  Fair value gains on financial instruments was $424 million
after a loss of $1.08 billion a year ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shaji Mathew in Dubai at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  